name: landsat-tm-and-etm-kansas-satellite-image-database-ksid
notes: The Kansas Satellite Image Database (KSID):2000-2001 consists of terrain-corrected, precision rectified spring, summer, and fall Landsat 5 Thematic Mapper (TM) and Landsat 7 Enhanced Thematic Mapper (ETM+) imagery covering the state of Kansas, tiled by county in GeoTiff format. While some county triplicates date wholly from either 2000 or 2001, some county triplicates were constructed using imagery from both 2000 and 2001. The KSID:2000-2001 consists of raw data and visual products. The raw dataset consists of the seven (TM)or eight (ETM+) geometrically corrected Landsat bands in their original units (DN values). The visual dataset consists of three products: Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) images, false-colorinfrared composites, and resolution-enhanced natural color composites.
